<h2 id="ê²Œì´íŠ¸ì›¨ì´">ê²Œì´íŠ¸ì›¨ì´</h2>
<p>ë‹¤ë¥¸ ë„¤íŠ¸ì›Œí¬ë¡œ ê°€ê¸°ìœ„í•œ í†µë¡œ</p>

<p>A traditional â€œgatewayâ€ can mean a device that (sometimes) is able to route traffic, but
whose primary goal is to <em>translate</em> from one protocol to another. For example- I would
use a â€œgatewayâ€ if I wanted to send packets from my IPv4 network to/from a IPv6 network,
or maybe an AppleTalk network to/from a Token Ring network.</p>

<p>ê²Œì´íŠ¸ì›¨ì´ëŠ” ê°œë…ì ì¸ ìš©ì–´, ë¼ìš°í„°ëŠ” ì¥ë¹„</p>

